      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — primary result",
      "description": "Detailed comparison of FEA-predicted construct stiffness against N=11 experimental measurements pooled across two independent laboratories. Mean experimental stiffness was 142.3 N/mm (SD 8.7 N/mm); FEA ensemble mean prediction was 138.6 N/mm, yielding a relative difference of 2.6%, well within the pre-specified 10% acceptance bound. The validation metric E/uval was computed as 0.84, below the 1.96 threshold. Uncertainty quantification accounted for material property scatter (titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V lot-to-lot variability ±3%), geometric tolerance stack-up (±0.05 mm on screw OD), and boundary-condition fidelity (UHMWPE block density ±5%). The three-laboratory FEA ensemble showed inter-code variability of less than 1.2% on stiffness, confirming numerical reproducibility. This result constitutes the primary evidentiary basis for the Accepted decision and is discussed extensively in the credibility assessment report (Nagaraja et al., 2022, Section 4.3). The generation workflow involved automated post-processing scripts executed within the FDA CDRH modeling environment; however, the structured provenance activity record linking this result to its generating computational process was not captured in the submission package.",
