    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs required level 2) is accepted on the basis that the COU is bounded to quasi-static bench characterization under ASTM F1717, the single test condition is the clinically and regulatorily specified reference condition, and all three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, relative difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the stated COU at Medium assurance level.",
